\cb5   \cf6 Introduction\cf4                                                                              \cb1 \
\cb5   \cf6 Welcome to the DeyeCloud OpenAPI Portal. The DeyeCloud system\'92s data is accessible \cf4       \cb1 \
\cb5   \cf6 securely and efficiently via API. The platform interface offers two primary operations:\cf4   \cb1 \
\cb5   \cf6 Monitoring Operation: Fetch station-level and device-level data, including historical \cf4    \cb1 \
\cb5   \cf6 and real-time data.\cf4                                                                       \cb1 \
\cb5   \cf6 Controlling Operation: Execute commands to control devices.\cf4                               \cb1 \
\cb5   \cf6 Station-level and device-level data (including history and live data) can be fetched \cf4     \cb1 \
\cb5   \cf6 through Monitoring Operations.\cf4                                                            \cb1 \
\cb5   \cf6 Controlling Operations can be used to commit the command to control the device.\cf4           \cb1 \
\cb5   \cf6 This document will guide you through the registration, setup, usage, and best practices \cf4  \cb1 \
\cb5   \cf6 for working with the DeyeCloud OpenAPI.\cf4                                                   \cb1 \
\cb5   \cf6 Create a DeyeCloud application\cf4                                                            \cb1 \
\cb5   \cf6 Obtain access token\cf4                                                                       \cb1 \
\cb5   \cf6 Invoke endpoints through access token\cf4                                                     \cb1 \
\cb5   \cf6 Create a DeyeCloud Application\cf4                                                            \cb1 \
\cb5   \cf6 To start, make sure you have completed the following steps:\cf4                               \cb1 \
\cb5   \cf6 1.  Create an account on DeyeCloud\cf4                                                        \cb1 \
\cb5   \cf6 To create a DeyeCloud Application, you must first have an account on DeyeCloud.\cf4           \cb1 \
\cb5   \cf6 Please remember which datacenter you choose when you register your DeyeCloud account.\cf4     \cb1 \
\cb5   \cf6 If you choose a data center in EU, the baseUrl (for the following endpoint invoking \cf4      \cb1 \
\cb5   \cf6 steps) is https://eu1-developer.deyecloud.com.\cf4                                            \cb1 \
\cb5   \cf6 If you choose a data center in US, the baseUrl (for the following endpoint invoking \cf4      \cb1 \
\cb5   \cf6 steps) is https://us1-developer.deyecloud.com.\cf4                                            \cb1 \
\cb5   \cf6 If you choose a data center in INDIA, the baseUrl (for the following endpoint invoking \cf4   \cb1 \
\cb5   \cf6 steps) is https://india-developer.deyecloud.com.\cf4                                          \cb1 \
\cb5   \cf6 Which data center should I choose?\cf4                                                        \cb1 \
\cb5   \cf6 Depending on the location of your devices:\cf4                                                \cb1 \
\cb5   \cf6 If your devices are in Europe, Africa, or the Asia-Pacific region, please choose the \cf4     \cb1 \
\cb5   \cf6 Europe data center.\cf4                                                                       \cb1 \
\cb5   \cf6 If your devices are in North or South America, please choose the Americas data center.\cf4    \cb1 \
\cb5   \cf6 2. Create a DeyeCloud application\cf4                                                         \cb1 \
\cb5   \cf6 Fill in the new Application form and create an application.\cf4                               \cb1 \
\cb5   \cf6 After creating an application, AppId&AppSecret will be assigned to you. Please save this\cf4  \cb1 \
\cb5   \cf6  information securely.\cf4                                                                    \cb1 \
\cb5   \cf6 Getting Started\cf4                                                                           \cb1 \
\cb5   \cf6 The below flow chart describes the flow of OpenAPI usage:\cf4                                 \cb1 \
\cb5   \cf6 Obtain Access Token\cf4                                                                       \cb1 \
